    {
      "id": "why-graphs",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Why graphs?",
      "position": {
        "x": -40,
        "y": 60
      },
      "width": 700,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Why graphs?\n\nA node can be anything: text, code, data, UI, API, AI model, video, live query.\n\nAn edge can mean anything: flows into, depends on, triggers, contains.\n\nYou decide what it means — and you can evolve it over time.\n\n**Capabilities**\n- 🌐 Web-native\n- 🤖 AI-first\n- ⚡ Executable\n- 📁 Portable\n- 🧬 Composable\n- 🧾 Git-friendly",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "html": "",
        "svg": "",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
